main event: A person in Columbus, Ohio reported seeing a strange object in the sky on September 13, 1966.
interesting points: The person's wife saw an object that she described as a web-like structure or a parachute, passing over their house at treetop height.
The object disappeared and then reappeared, moving more rapidly the second time.
The person's dog barked wildly at the object, which may indicate the dog sensed something unusual.
The person consulted with a physician, ophthalmologist, and psychiatrist to get their opinions on the sighting, as his wife was reluctant to report it initially.
The Project Blue Book investigative officer stated that nothing quite like this had been previously reported.
sighted object: a web-like structure or parachute-like object
photographs: no photographs included in the report
